Comments: Genome sequencing as part of The One Thousand Microbial Genomes Phase 4 (KMG IV) project
Genome sequencing of Purple Non-Sulfur Bacteria to expand its genomic potential for discovery

The order Rhodobacterales represents one of the most investigated bacterial groups. It encompasses a highly phenotypically, metabolically and ecologically diverse group of species expressing many important metabolic activities. To better understand the origin of such metabolic variability we sequenced genomes of three closely related haloalkaliphilic species differing in their phototrophic capacity and oxygen preference: photoheterotrophic and facultatively anaerobic bacterium Rhodobaca barguzinensis, aerobic photoheterotrophic Roseinatronobacter thiooxidans and aerobic facultatively lithoautotrophic bacterium 'Natronohydrobacter thiooxidans'.

Sequencing Center: Institute for Biodiversity and Ecosystem dynamics, Faculty of Science, University of Amsterdam
